'''Level 590''', often referred to as '''"Unforgettable Celestial Journey"''', is the 591<sup>st</sup> level of The Backrooms, which is an extremely vast highway located in the sky.

== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 30pt; color: #cc7a99">Description</span></center> ==
{{Blurimage|file=Evening road in the sky 1.jpg|caption=Level 590 landscape, as soon as a wanderer enters it in the evening.}}
As soon as the wanderer reaches the level, he finds himself in a random car from the [[The Frontrooms|Frontrooms]], manufactured approximately between the 1970s and the present day. At times, a wanderer may find themselves driving the only car for many miles, while at other times, they might become stuck in traffic due to the presence of other cars on the level, which are driven either by autopilot or neutral adult [[Entity 9|Facelings]]. 
Often, the autopilot may not be present in the original car from the Frontrooms. The probability of a car accident is low because Faceling drivers behave sensibly and the autopilot is well-trained, with some studies suggesting it possesses [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_general_intelligence Artificial General Intelligence] (AGI) comparable to human intelligence; however, this does not account for the possibility that a wanderer may provoke an accident.

Road signs, comparably rare at this level, are road signs found in the Frontrooms in the USA, but their content will contradict reality there. For example, the left exit may lead to "Home Street" and the right exit to "Paradise Road." If the word "EXIT" is not written in the upper left corner of the road sign, it means that this sign has no informational value, but if this word is present on it, it means that the road will lead the participant to a certain level after a specified number of miles, depending on the name of the street/road/any other object to which the exit leads.

The level has a 12-hour evening and a 12-hour day. The exact source of illumination at Level 590 is unknown for certain; on the Evening Road, there may be no visible light source at all, or there may be a full (or partial) moon shining purple, or a blurry, dazzling white spot. On the Daytime Road, there is a constant source of light—an exact copy of the sun from the Frontrooms, or a crescent moon.

In the "evening," the road is a concrete and wooden platform approximately two meters high, surrounded on both sides by a white brick fence somewhere about 20–30 centimeters high. There is a phenomenon that is not considered equivalent to other phenomena of this level, representing a significant change in the appearance of the road every few hours. The most common changes are the appearance of several more lanes, where the opposite (left) side of the road will be fenced off from the right side, and the appearance of road signs attached to metal pipes. During the day, the road has only three lanes, and the fence becomes higher.
== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 30pt; color: #cc7a99">Phenomena</span></center> ==
The phenomenon of "road disappearance" has only been observed during the daytime. Before it begins, the sky will become covered with large cumulus clouds, and then the road will slowly and gradually disappear: first the lanes and sidewalk will vanish, then the cars, and finally the road itself. A person will no longer feel the ground beneath their feet and will begin to float in the air; to move, they will have to use the same movements as when swimming. It is possible to move upward indefinitely, but if one tries to see what is under the clouds, one will reach [[Level 113]]. In rare cases, the road may disappear completely suddenly, without the appearance of multiple clouds.

On the contrary, "ghost cars" only appear in the evening. Although they initially look like ordinary cars, over time their headlights and engine sounds will disappear, and then the car itself will begin to fade, and the Faceling driver will vanish. After a while, the car will stop, and if a wanderer gets in, he can try to start it again, but some functions will not work. For example, the radio will only make noise, the handbrake will be locked, and the windows will not open. This car will behave extremely erratically when restarted, including sudden acceleration and braking, which often leads to accidents. Eventually, the car disappears completely, and a wanderer is left standing in the middle of the road. This phenomenon is commonly explained as "the dissipation of energy in the particles that make up the car."

In addition, thunderstorms may occasionally occur at this level, which then leads to the phenomenon of "road destruction." Before the thunder, clouds will begin to move closer to the road, and then lightning will appear on them, striking the asphalt and causing the road to collapse. The loud thunder will be deafening, and the lightning will cause flashes of light that will blind a wanderer for a few seconds. The asphalt will begin to make crunching sounds and then crack; some pieces will fall into the Void, and if the traveler falls, they will end up on Level 113. It is almost impossible to remain on the level during a thunderstorm, and in some cases, wanderers have even died from being struck by lightning. Those who remained on the level during this phenomenon reported that after a while, the clouds began to disperse, the sounds became quieter, the lightning decreased, and the road began to recover, although cracks remained in the asphalt.

== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 30pt; color: #cc7a99">Colonies and Outposts</span></center> ==
<center>Due to the level being affected by [[Phenomenon 15]], it is impossible to meet other wanderers here and, therefore, to establish colonies or outposts.</center>

== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 30pt; color: #cc7a99">Entrances and Exits</span></center> ==
=== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 20pt; color: #cc7a99">Entrances</span></center> ===
* Various factors in [[Level 83.1]];
* Clouds appear, fog dissipates, and the environment turns pink or white in [[Level 690]].
=== <center><span style="font-family: Leckerli One; font-size: 20pt; color: #cc7a99">Exits</span></center> ===
* When leaving the highway onto a certain road or street, one can reach a specific level (for example, Home Street leads to [[The End]], Paradise Road to [[Level 399]], and Moon Street to [[Level 700]]);
* Falling into the abyss will lead to [[Level 113]];
* If the environment begins to darken, as if night is falling, a wanderer will end up on [[Level 400]].

